Description: A sealing from a document, the imprint from which survives at the rear: three impressions from the same intaglio gem, with Harpokrates standing to left, finger to mouth, holding a cornucopia. Unfired pale yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3636)
